Wash and dry all produce. Halve, peel, and dice @yellow onion{1}(halved, peeled, and diced). Heat a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon} in a large, tall-sided pan over medium-high heat. Add onion and @smoky Mexican seasoning{1%tbsp} (we'll be using the rest later). Toss until softened and fragrant, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @basmati rice{1.5%cup} and toss to coat.

Stir @water{3%cups} and @gluten free chicken demi glace{1} into pan. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and let simmer until rice is tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Remove from heat and keep covered until rest of meal is ready.

Meanwhile, halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{8%ounce}. Halve, pit, and scoop flesh from @avocado{1}, then thinly slice. Pick @cilantro{1/4%ounce} leaves from stems; discard stems. Zest @lime{1} until you have 1/4 tsp zest, then cut into halves. Cut one half into wedges. Mince or grate @garlic{1%clove} until you have 1/4 tsp.

== Lime Crema ==

In a #small bowl{}, stir together @sour cream{6%tablespoon}, lime zest, juice from half the lime, @water{2%tbsp}, and a pinch of garlic. Add more water as needed to achieve a drizzly consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Chicken ==

Heat a large drizzle of oil in another #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Season @chicken tenders{24%ounce} all over with salt, pepper, and remaining @smoky Mexican seasoning{1%tbsp}. Add chicken to pan and cook until browned and no longer pink in center, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> Work in batches to help chicken brown and avoid overcrowding.

== To Serve ==

Fluff rice with a fork and season with salt and pepper. Divide between plates. Top with chicken, tomatoes, and avocado.

> Arrange the avocado slices like a fan for a pretty presentation.

Drizzle with crema and sprinkle with cilantro. Serve with lime wedges for squeezing over.